<main id="main">
    <h1>Credit notes</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, you can generate credit notes as PDF files, for example if you want to print them or send them to your customers as an email attachment.<br>
Use credit notes to grant customers additional discounts for orders that have already been paid or if refunds have to be arranged due to returned items.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Default settings for credit notes</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Carry out the desired default settings once in the menu <strong>System » System settings » Aufträge » Einstellungen</strong> and save them before generating credit notes. This is required for the correct application of your desired default settings for the <strong>Standard status for credit notes</strong> and the inclusion of shipping costs in credit notes. For further information on carrying out standard settings for orders, refer to the <a href="/en/orders/basic-settings">Basic settings</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">1. Setting up a document template for credit notes</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Before generating credit notes, you have to set up a document template. This is done in the menu <strong>System » System settings » Client » Select client » Locations » Select location » Documents</strong>.<br>
For further information and instructions on setting up the document template, refer to the <a href="/en/orders/order-documents">Order documents</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="300">2. Generating a single credit note</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can manually generate a single credit note in the corresponding credit note order, if necessary. For further information and instructions on generating credit note orders, refer to the <a href="/en/orders/managing-orders#530">Generating a credit note</a> chapter of the manual.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Generating a single credit note:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Edit orders</strong>.<br>
→ The order overview opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the credit note order for which a credit note should be created by clicking on the <strong>Order ID</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Receipts</strong> tab.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Create receipt</strong> drop-down menu, select the document <strong>Credit note</strong>.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to <a href="#table-credit-note-order-receipts-credit-note">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings to generate the credit note.<br>
→ A <strong>PDF file</strong> containing the generated credit note opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
